2.0 What does the insurance cover?
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
:FED.
2.1 Coverage
:SKRSLUT.
.br
2.1.1 The insurance covers functional defects, i.e. 'internal damage'.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.1.2 The insurance covers selected consumer electronics (Hi-Fi
systems, TVs, games consoles, cameras, video cameras, DVD players,
computers, GPS units and the like (see Article 2.1.3, however, and
the exceptions listed in Article 3.1) that are located in Denmark
(own residence or holiday home) and whose purchase price exceeds DKK
500 (including VAT, but excluding delivery costs) on condition that
the insured paid the full purchase price with his/her card. For
insured persons resident on Greenland or the Faeroe Islands, the
items must be located in their residence there.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.1.3 The insurance only covers new items purchased with the insured's
MasterCard Silver card from a VAT-registered or correspondingly
registered dealer in Denmark. For insured persons resident on Greenland
or the Faeroe Islands, purchases made there are also covered by the
insurance. The purchase of items over the Internet is covered on
condition the website is based in Denmark and subject to the Danish
Sale of Goods Act, or based in Greenland or the Faeroe Islands and
subject to the Greenlandic or Faeroese Sale of Goods Act.
.sp 3mm
.of 5mm
*¤The insurance provides coverage for a period of up to two years after
the time at which the right to complain to the seller ceases, see
Section 83 of the Danish Sale of Goods Act.
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤The insurance coverage comes into effect at the time where the policy
holder's right to claim faults/defects against the seller has ceased
pursuant to Section 83 of the Danish Sale of Goods Act (the purchase
must be covered by the Danish Sale of Goods Act or, if the insured is
resident on Greenland or the Faeroe Islands, by the Greenlandic or
Faeroese Sale of Goods Act). For insured persons resident in Denmark,
this means at least two years after the object of the sale has been
transferred to the purchaser, while the deadline for insured persons
resident on Greenland or the Faeroe Islands is one year after said
date.
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤If the dealer has provided a longer complaints period than the
standard period stated in the Danish Sale of Goods Act - see Section 83
of said Act - the extended complaints deadline shall apply in relation
to this insurance as from the time when the dealer's extended
complaints period terminates, and with a reduced period such that the
total complaints period (the complaints period provided by the dealer
plus the extended complaints period in accordance with this insurance
policy) does not exceed four years.
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤If the insured cancels his/her card - or if the insurance coverage
ceases due to termination or similar of the working relationship between
the bank and the insurance provider - items purchased using the card are
still covered according to the present insurance terms and conditions
for up to two years subsequent to the expiry of the original deadline
for filing complaints regarding the item insured.
.of
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
